 News of the arrests was met with relief by Louvre visitors and passersby on Sunday. “It’s important for our heritage. A week later, it does feel a bit late, we wonder how this could even happen — but it was important that the guys were caught,” said Freddy Jacquemet.  “I think the main thing now is whether they can recover the jewels,” added Diana Ramirez. “That’s what really matters.” ___ Petrequin reported from London.

